# Docker is the recommended default runtime for Symphony Elixir.
# Configure this file for the primary container-based path.

# Repo bootstrap and dashboard settings:
SYMPHONY_DASHBOARD_PORT=4000
SYMPHONY_WORKFLOW_FILE=./WORKFLOW.trello.docker.md
SYMPHONY_SOURCE_REPO_URL=https://github.com/your-org/your-private-repo.git
GITHUB_TOKEN=
GITHUB_OWNER=
GITHUB_REPO=
GITHUB_PROJECT_NUMBER=
SYMPHONY_OPERATOR_TOKEN=
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=Symphony
GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=symphony@local.invalid
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME=Symphony
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL=symphony@local.invalid

# Use `./WORKFLOW.trello.docker.md` for Trello or `./WORKFLOW.github.docker.md` for GitHub Projects v2.
# GitHub tracker mode additionally needs GITHUB_OWNER, GITHUB_REPO, and GITHUB_PROJECT_NUMBER.
# The bundled Trello Docker workflow now defaults to PR landing, so it also needs
# GITHUB_OWNER and GITHUB_REPO, plus a GITHUB_TOKEN that can clone, push, and create PRs.
# You can also leave it blank initially and store a write-only token later from `/settings`.
# The container image configures an in-container Git credential helper for https://github.com
# so normal git clone / fetch / push calls use this token automatically.
# `SYMPHONY_SOURCE_REPO_URL` and the Git author/committer identity can also be overridden later
# from the dashboard settings page.
# Host-local workflows still exist, but they are the fallback path rather than the recommended default.
# Codex auth is stored inside the named Docker volume `symphony_codex_home` after
# you run `docker compose run --rm symphony codex login` once.
# Set SYMPHONY_OPERATOR_TOKEN if you want to approve guardrail actions or start Codex device auth
# directly from the dashboard.
